"Laue H.J.","The impact of heat pumps on global warming and ozone depletion",1994,"Heat Recovery Systems and CHP","14","3",,"323","335",,,10.1016/0890-4332(94)90028-0,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0028427303&partnerID=40&md5=c79fad4a367045600ee1fd400fede447","Informationsz Wärmepumpen u Kältetechnik, Fachinformationszentrum Karlsruhe D-7514 Eggenstein-Leopoldshafen 2, Germany","Laue, H.J., Informationsz Wärmepumpen u Kältetechnik, Fachinformationszentrum Karlsruhe D-7514 Eggenstein-Leopoldshafen 2, Germany","The heat pump, a proven and reliable technology, has the potential to reduce primary energy consumption and the corresponding CO2-emissions for heating and cooling in domestic, commercial and industrial applications. The basic principles of heat pump technology and the anthrogenic CO2-formation under the given energy supply and demand situation in Europe and the related impact on global warming are described. An analysis of the energy flow between primary energy exploitation and the useful energy of different heating systems clearly demonstrates the ability of electric heat pumps to reduce primary energy consumption in Europe between 15 and 50%, compared with oil- and gas-heating systems. The corresponding reduction of CO2-emissions will be between 20 and 60% and up to 85% of other pollutants. The present status of alternative working fluids which do not contribute to ozone depletion is presented and the direct (working fluids) and indirect (energy consumption) impact of different heat pumps on the greenhouse effect is discussed. © 1994.",,"Energy conservation; Environmental impact; Greenhouse effect; Heating; Ozone layer; Alternative working fluids; Energy consumption; Global warming; Ozone depletion; Heat pump systems",,,,,,"Fritsche, Umweltanalyse von Energie-, (1993) Umweltanalyse von Energie-, Transort- und Stoffsystemen: Gesamt-Emissions-Modell Integrierter Systeme (EMIS) Version 2.0 Hessisches Ministrium für Umwelt, , Energie und Bundesangelegenheiten Weisbaden; Praxisbezogene Untersuchung zu Energiebedarf und Emissionen verschiedener Heizungs-systeme im Wohnungsbau (1993) Vereinigung Deutscher Elektrizitätswerke—VDEW e. V.; Laue, Fuel Cycle Analysis (1993) 4th IEA Heat Pump Conference, , 26–29 April, Maastricht, The Netherlands; Laue, Bedeutungder Wärmepumpe zur Energieeinsparung und CO2-Emissions-minderung. 4. (1993) VDEW-Chefgespräch: Elektrowärmepumpen-Umweltentlastung durch rationelle Stromanwendung, , 10.06.93 Darmstadt; Informationszentrum Wärmepumpen und Kältetechnik (IZW), Karlsruhe, unpublished resultsFrehn, Propan als alternatives Kältemittel—erste Betriebserfahrungen (1993) Wärmepumpe März S. 1. Informationszentrum Wärmepumpen und Kältetechnik (IZW), , Karlsruhe; Reiners, VEW-Test erfolgreich: Wärmepumpe ohne FCKW, Wärmepumpe Juni (1993) S. 3. Informationszentrum Wärmepumpen und Kältetechnik (IZW), , Karlsruhe; AFEAS, (1991) US DOE: Energy and Global Warming of CFC Alternative Technologies, , 3FEAS, Washington DC","Laue, H.J.; Informationsz Wärmepumpen u Kältetechnik, Fachinformationszentrum Karlsruhe D-7514 Eggenstein-Leopoldshafen 2, Germany",,,,,,,,08904332,,,,"English",,Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0028427303
